\begin_layout Subsection
Course description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This course is intended to provide a rigorous introduction to the study
 of industry and firm behavior.
 We will explore the relationships among firms in an industry or across
 industries by examining the nature of strategic interaction.
 In particular we study firms' choices of price, quantity and quality in
 scenarios where the assumptions of perfect competition do not hold.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Prerequisite:
\series default
 ECON or BNEC.
 (ECON 339 or ECON 276) and (ECON 300 or ECON 361).
\end_layout

